  <h1>dylburger.com</h1>
  <h2>Asian Burger Recipe</h2>
  <p>Makes 6-8 burgers</p>
  <ul id="burger_recipe">
    <li>2 lbs ground beef</li>
    <li>1 lb ground pork</li>
    <li>4 cloves garlic</li>
    <li>2 shallots</li>
    <li>1/2 cup chopped green onions (half for meat, half for garnish)</li>
    <li>1 cup Shiitake mushrooms</li>
    <li>3 tbsp Gochujang (Korean hot pepper paste)</li>
    <li>2 tbsp soy sauce</li>
    <li>1 tsp crushed fennel</li>
    <li>1 tsp Chinese Five Spice</li>
    <li>1 tsp ground ginger</li>
    <li>1 tsp crushed chili peppers</li>
    <li>1/2 tsp nutmeg</li>
    <li>1/2 tsp pepper</li>
    <li>Wasabi to taste</li>
  </ul>
  <br />
  <ol>
    <li>Wipe shiitake mushrooms with wet paper towel to clean. Chop mushrooms, garlic and shallots finely. Cook mushrooms in sesame oil over medium heat until tender, about 5 min. After mushrooms are cooked, toss in garlic and shallots and cook for 2 min.</li>
    <li>Grind fennel with mortar and pestle, mix remaining spices.</li>
    <li>Mix beef, pork, mushrooms, garlic, shallots, 1/4 cup green onions, Gochujang, soy sauce, spices together well. Form into 6-8 patties. Let sit in fridge for at least 1 hour.</li>
    <li>Cook over open flame, toast bun. Spread additional Gochujang paste on top of burger, garnish with remaining green onions. Spread small amount of wasabi paste on bun to taste. Enjoy.</li>
  <br />
